 Agents 2 and 3 appear to have reviewed and revised a different piece of code related to code efficiency analysis, which is not directly relevant to the `Multi-Agent Drift Championship` game.\n\nTo summarize and provide a coherent final output, I will focus on the initial implementation started by Agent 1 and make necessary adjustments to ensure it aligns with the project requirements. Here is the revised and extended version of `solution.py`:\n\n```json\n{\n  "solution.py": "```python\\n# solution.py\\n\\n# Import necessary libraries\\nimport random\\nimport math\\n\\nclass Track:\\n    def __init__(self, name, length, width):\\n        self.name = name\\n        self.length = length\\n        self.width = width\\n        self.obstacles = []\\n\\n    def add_obstacle(self, position, type):\\n        self.obstacles.append((position, type))\\n\\n    def get_random_position(self):\\n        return (random.uniform(0, self.length), random.uniform(0, self.width))\\n\\nclass AIAgent:\\n    def __init__(self, name, position, speed, drift_skill):\\n        self.name = name\\n        self.position = position\\n        self.speed = speed\\n        self.drift_skill = drift_skill\\n        self.angle = 0  # Angle of the car\\n\\n    def move(self, direction, distance):\\n        # Update position based on direction and distance\\n        self.position = (self.position[0] + distance * math.cos(self.angle),\\n                         self.position[1] + distance * math.sin(self.angle))\\n\\n    def drift(self, angle_change):\\n        # Update angle based on drift skill and angle change\\n        self.angle += angle_change * self.drift_skill\\n\\n    def check_collision(self, track):\\n        # Simple collision detection with track boundaries\\n        x, y = self.position\\n        if x < 0 or x > track.length or y < 0 or y > track.width:\\n            return True\\n        return False\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\"__main__\\":\\n    track = Track(\\"Drift Track\\", 